Privacy Policy for RESTRAIN

Last updated: January 2026

RESTRAIN is a free arcade game. Your privacy is important to us, and this Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the app.

1. Information We Collect

RESTRAIN itself does not collect or store any personal information directly.

However, the app uses third-party services that may collect limited information as part of their normal operation.

These services may collect:

Device information (such as device model, operating system version)

Advertising identifiers

Gameplay scores (for leaderboard purposes)

Crash and performance data

2. Third-Party Services Used

RESTRAIN uses the following third-party services:

Google Play Games Services

Used to provide:

Leaderboards

Player sign-in

Google Play Games Services may collect and process data in accordance with Google’s Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

Google AdMob

Used to display ads in the app.

AdMob may collect:

Advertising identifiers

Approximate location

Interaction with ads

Google AdMob’s privacy policy can be found here:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

3. How Information Is Used

Information collected by third-party services is used to:

Display ads

Provide leaderboard functionality

Improve app stability and performance

Detect crashes and technical issues

RESTRAIN does not sell, rent, or share personal data directly.

4. Data Storage

RESTRAIN does not operate its own servers.

Any data collected is handled and stored by the third-party services listed above in accordance with their respective privacy policies.

5. Children’s Privacy

RESTRAIN does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

If you believe that a child has provided personal information through a third-party service used by this app, please contact Google directly using the links above.

6. Your Choices

You can:

Opt out of personalized ads through your device settings

Control Google Play Games Services access via your Google account

Disable ads by purchasing any available ad-removal option (if provided)

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.

Any changes will be reflected by updating the “Last updated” date at the top of this page.

8. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the developer through the email address provided on the Google Play Store listing.
